title: For Sale:  KRICO 340 S ST .22 LR In. 24 inch Bolt Action Rifles
location: North Carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent: This is an extremely rare rifle with well documented provenance. In the 1980's, German premium builder Krico (Krieqeskorte), developed a .22 lr version of the company's excellent Model 640, .308 winchester sniper rifle. A true "Mini-Sniper", the model 340 S ST mirror features of the model 640, to include a factory-installed birdcage flash suppressor, generous stippling on the grip and forearm, and seven ventilation slits along both sides of the forearm. Due to its premium price, few model 340 S ST "Mini-Sniper" rifles were improted, and none since 1989 when it apparently went out of production. Despite its name, this rifle has the heft and feel of a full- size rifle - the "mini" term refers to its .22 lr chambering, not its size.I will have this ship

The 5R rifling profile increases barrel life expectancy, accuracy and creates less fouling and bullet deformation over time Whether you're a benchrest shooter or longtime, look no further for better reliability and precision. Why 5-R? 5-R rifling is the same type of rifiling used on the battle proven M-24 SWS. There are 5 lands as opposed to the normal 6 land configuration. title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant 1891/59
postcontent: Model 1891/59 Carbine: Commonly called "91/59s," the M1891/59s were created by shortening M1891/30 rifles to carbine length, with rear sight numbers partially ground off to reflect reduced range. These rifles are almost clones of the M38 except for the ground off M91/30 rear sight.The "1891/59" marking on the receiver suggests the carbines were created in or after 1959. It was initially thought that Bulgaria or another Soviet satellite country performed the conversions in preparation for a Western invasion that never came. Recent evidence suggests that the M91/59 was indeed produced in Bulgaria from Soviet-supplied wartime production M91/30s. Total production of the 91/59 is uncertain; figures as low as one million and as high as three million have appeared in firearm literature.asking 250 obo, any cash offers are welcome
